          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1679405526377-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the gnocchi is cooking, heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) over a high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>and a small knob of<strong> butter</strong></p><p>Once melted, add the <strong>sliced onion</strong>,<strong> sliced mushrooms </strong>and<strong> dried thyme</strong></p><p>Add 75ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[100ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[125ml]</span> <strong>cold</strong> <strong>water </strong>and cook, covered, for 8-10 min or until the onions and mushrooms are completely softened, stirring occasionally</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1679405530591-x200.jpg",
